column1: # Name: Share of contributing family workers, Total

# Definition: Share of female and male contributing family workers. Contributing family workers are those workers who hold “self-employment jobs” as own-account workers in a market-oriented establishment operated by a related person living in the same household.
# Source: International Labour Organization (ILO) Key Indicators of the Labour Market (KILM)
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
